<div class="ai-conversation-banner">
  <div class="banner-wrapper">
    <h1 class="brand-alt-h1">
      Bot-Assisted Oral History Search
    </h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="text-page">
  <p class="fs-4 mt-3">
    Find themes or topics discussed in our
    <%= link_to "oral history collection", oral_histories_collection_path %> using this AI-powered software tool to identify passages from transcripts.
  </p>

  <details class="mb-3 ai-conversation-help">
    <summary class="text-link">Tips for using this tool</summary>

    <div class="p-3">
      <p>Enter a research question about what is in our oral histories, and this tool will use AI technologies to try to answer, based only on information it finds in the interview transcripts.</p>

      <ul class="mb-2">
        <li>List interviewees who…</li>
        <li>I'm looking for experiencies about…</li>
        <li>Which interviewees…</li>
        <li>Is there any discussion of…</li>
        <li>Can you tell me about…</li>
      </ul>

      Or, just describe in your own words what you're looking for. If the tool can't find enough, you might try asking a broader more general question.
    </div>
  </details>

  <%= simple_form_for :"", url: oral_history_ai_conversation_index_path, method: :post do |f| %>

    <%= f.text_area :q, class: "form-control text mb-3", data: { ai_conversation_q: true }, required: true, rows: 3 %>

    <div class="d-flex justify-content-end">
      <%= f.button :submit, "Ask", class: "btn btn-brand-main" %>
    </div>

    <div>
      <%= f.input :access_limit, as: :radio_buttons, required: false,
            collection: [
              ['immediate_ohms_only', "Only those with synchronized audio (OHMS) — #{@immediate_ohms_only_count}"],
              ['immediate_only', "Only those fully public (do not require request) — #{@immediate_only_count}"],
              ['immediate_or_automatic', "Both fully public and those with automatically approved request — #{@immediate_or_automatic_count}"],
              ['', "All: Includes those which require request approval — #{@all_count}"]
            ],
            label_method: ->(item) { item[1].html_safe },
            value_method: ->(item) { item[0] },
            checked: '',
            label: "Which Oral Histories to consider in search" %>
    </div>

  <% end %>

  <details class="mb-3 ai-conversation-help">
    <summary class="text-link">Some details about how this tool works</summary>

    <div class="p-3">
      <%= render "technical_details" %>
   </div>
  </details>

  <div class="alert alert-warning">
    <i class="fa fa-flag me-2" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    This is currently a <b>beta test</b> under active research & development, available only to internal Science History Institute users and invited guests.
  </div>

</div>
